      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: summarize gateway startup sidecars",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fixes #14861.\n- Add a small redacted Gateway startup outcome summary after sidecars settle and before readiness is logged.\n- Surface the missing Gmail watcher account case as `gmail-watcher=skipped (no gmail account configured)`.\n- Keep raw exception details, accounts, provider details, command args, tokens, and local paths out of the summary.\n\n## AI assistance disclosure\n\nThis PR was implemented with AI assistance. I reviewed the change and understand the affected Gateway post-attach sidecar path.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Gateway boot now reports a concise redacted sidecar/hook outcome summary, including the Gmail watcher skipped reason when hooks are enabled but `hooks.gmail.account` is absent.\n\nReal environment tested: Actual `pnpm openclaw gateway run` from this branch, with isolated home/state/config, loopback port, fake gateway/hook tokens, hooks enabled, and no Gmail account configured.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nHOME=<isolated-home> \\\nOPENCLAW_HOME=<isolated-home> \\\nOPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=<isolated-state-dir> \\\nOPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=<isolated-config> \\\nOPENCLAW_SKIP_CHANNELS=1 \\\nOPENCLAW_SKIP_PROVIDERS=1 \\\nOPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=<redacted-gateway-token> \\\npnpm openclaw gateway run --allow-unconfigured --auth token --token <redacted-gateway-token> --port 19661 --tailscale off --ws-log compact\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n[gateway] startup summary: internal-hooks=skipped (not configured); channels=skipped (disabled by environment); plugin-services=started; internal-startup-hook=skipped (not configured); gateway-start-hooks=skipped (not configured); memory-qmd=skipped (not configured); gmail-watcher=skipped (no gmail account configured); gmail-model=skipped (not configured)\n[gateway] ready\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The gateway reaches readiness and the startup log includes the fixed Gmail watcher skipped reason without account names, paths, command args, provider details, or tokens.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live Gmail Pub/Sub watcher with a real Gmail account; this patch only changes startup outcome reporting and does not change Gmail delivery behavior.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`startGatewaySidecars` only scheduled the Gmail watcher when both hooks were enabled and `hooks.gmail.account` was configured. When hooks were enabled but the account was missing, the watcher path was skipped before the lifecycle helper ran. The lifecycle helper also intentionally suppresses expected non-start reasons such as `no gmail account configured`, so startup had no concise user-visible outcome for that subsystem.\n\n## Dependency contract\n\nNo upstream dependency behavior changed. The relevant internal contract is in `src/hooks/gmail-watcher-lifecycle.ts`: `startGmailWatcherWithLogs` returns early for `OPENCLAW_SKIP_GMAIL_WATCHER`, delegates to `startGmailWatcher`, and suppresses warnings for `hooks not enabled` and `no gmail account configured`. The fix records the same config/env decision before scheduling the post-ready sidecar.\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- `pnpm test src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.test.ts src/hooks/gmail-watcher-lifecycle.test.ts src/gateway/server-startup-log.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/gateway/server-startup-outcomes.ts src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.ts src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Security Impact\n\nLow. The summary uses fixed subsystem IDs and fixed reason strings only. Tests cover redaction for Gmail account values and raw failure details.\n\n## Human Verification\n\nI inspected the issue discussion, related open PR #61704, closed PR search results for `14861`, current Gateway startup code, Gmail watcher lifecycle code, and the focused diff. The open PR does not implement this startup summary.\n\n## CODEOWNERS / owner review\n\nTouched files are under `src/gateway/` and do not match the current secops-only Gateway CODEOWNERS patterns for auth, secret, or security files. Normal Gateway maintainer review is expected.\n\n## Changelog\n\nContributor PR: `CHANGELOG.md` not edited. Maintainers can decide whether this startup diagnostics improvement needs a changelog entry during landing.\n\n## Review conversations\n\nNo PR review conversations yet. Issue comments from `@steipete` and `@clawsweeper` requested a narrow, redacted startup outcome summary and specifically called out the Gmail watcher missing-account blind spot.\n\n## Risks\n\nThe summary line adds one extra Gateway startup log entry. If maintainers want fewer subsystem entries, the formatter can be kept while narrowing the collected outcome list.\n\n## Behavior tradeoffs\n\nThe summary says `gmail-watcher=scheduled` when a Gmail account is configured because the actual watcher runs as a post-ready sidecar. Later asynchronous watcher failures still use the existing lifecycle warnings instead of blocking Gateway readiness.\n\n## Scope boundaries\n\nThis does not add a dashboard, new telemetry surface, config migration, dependency, provider inspection, or live Gmail validation. It preserves optional sidecar behavior and readiness semantics.\n\n## Validation\n\n- PASS: `pnpm test src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.test.ts src/hooks/gmail-watcher-lifecycle.test.ts src/gateway/server-startup-log.test.ts`\n- PASS: `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/gateway/server-startup-outcomes.ts src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.ts src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.test.ts`\n- PASS: `git diff --check`\n- PASS: `OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_LOCK_SCOPE=worktree pnpm check:changed`\n- PASS: real foreground Gateway startup proof with isolated state/config produced the redacted Gmail watcher skipped summary and reached `[gateway] ready`.\n- BLOCKED: `codex review --base origin/main` was attempted twice, but the Codex subprocess exited with code `-1` before producing findings.\n",
        "branch": "codex/14861-gateway-boot-summary",
